    "# ðŸš€ 5.1 Bayesian Methods\n",
    "\n",
    "Go Bayesian like a hippo sage! ðŸ¦› In this notebook, weâ€™ll estimate true nutrient intakes using priors and posteriors, perfect for nutrition studies like NDNS analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What weâ€™ll cover**:\n",
    "- **Bayesian Basics**: Combine prior knowledge with data to get posteriors.\n",
    "- **PyMC**: A Python tool to model nutrient intakes.\n",
    "- **Why care?** Bayesian methods handle uncertainty in small nutrition datasets.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Letâ€™s dive in!** Weâ€™ll model iron intakes for hippos using data from `hippo_nutrients.csv`.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details>\n",
    "<summary>ðŸ¤” Advanced: Why Bayesian?</summary>\n",
    "Bayesian methods shine for small samples or when you have strong priors (e.g., RDA for iron). Compare to frequentist in 4.4!\n",
    "</details>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up your Bayesian kitchen\n",
    "%pip install pymc pandas numpy matplotlib  # Install if on Colab\n",
    "import pymc as pm\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "print('Ready to model like a hippo sage! ðŸ¦›')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "load_data",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ðŸ§¬ Load Hippo Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Weâ€™ll use `hippo_nutrients.csv` to get iron intakes. Letâ€™s load and inspect it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "load",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "   ID Nutrient  Year  Value  Age Sex\n",
      "0  H1     Iron  2024    8.2   25   F\n",
      "1  H1     Iron  2025    8.5   26   F\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data_handling/data/hippo_nutrients.csv')\n",
    "iron_data = df[df['Nutrient'] == 'Iron']['Value'].dropna()\n",
    "print(df.head(2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bayesian",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ðŸ“Š Bayesian Model for Iron\n",
    "\n",
    "Weâ€™ll assume iron intake follows a normal distribution with a prior mean of 8 mg (based on RDA) and estimate the true mean.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Exercise 1**: Run the Bayesian model below to estimate hippo iron intake."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "model",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "with pm.Model() as model:\n",
    "    mu = pm.Normal('mu', mu=8, sigma=2)  # Prior: mean ~ N(8, 2)\n",
    "    sigma = pm.HalfNormal('sigma', sigma=1)\n",
    "    obs = pm.Normal('obs', mu=mu, sigma=sigma, observed=iron_data)\n",
    "    trace = pm.sample(1000, return_inferencedata=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot posterior\n",
    "plt.hist(trace['mu'], bins=30, density=True)\n",
    "plt.title('Posterior of Hippo Iron Intake ðŸ¦›')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Mean Iron (mg)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "exercise",
